<p><placeName>Herculaneum</placeName>, <date when="1814-12-12">Decr. 12th 1814</date></p>

<p>Dear Sir</p>

<p>Your Draft in favour of <persName>J. T. Wilkinson</persName> for 3000 lb of lead I
have paid&#8212;and have Aliso paid him a Due Bill in favour of <persName>Burges</persName>
for 240 lb of lead&#8212;which <persName>Mr Wilkinson</persName> told me that you promised
to give him; but if it does not meet you[r] approbation he is to
Endorse it on a Receipt which I give him&#8212;he is to Settle with you
the hawling of the Same&#8212;</p>

<p>I Enclose you a Letter&#8212;which I received from <persName>Mr Kerr</persName> you will
bee so good as to give him an answer</p>

<p>I send you the Accot of the lead sent in since I have been Sick</p>

<p>By <persName>Mr Haynes</persName> two loads&#8212;of 50 and 35 Bars Each________________________	3630

By <persName>Mr Landers</persName> One d°&#8212;of 50 __________________________________________	2107

By <persName>Burr Brown</persName> One d°&#8212;of 53___________________________________________	2213
												_____
												7950</p>

<p><persName>Elias Bates</persName>    [Rubric]</p>

<p>I have paid <persName>Mr Mitchel</persName> the 566 lb Lead&#8212;</p>

<p><persName>E. B</persName></p>

<p>[Addressed] <persName>Mr Moses Austin</persName> <placeName>Mine Burton</placeName></p>

        </div1>
    </body>
